		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />well im back to nes emulation scene.. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />I just want some tips to make rendering faster, when i rip off rendering from the emulator, that means not to display anything to screen the emu (cpu, ppu, apu, etc) takes 4%~ of cpu time when i turn it on it takes 35%~ in a Pentium 4 2.8, visual c compiled and optimized at maximum (of course).
<br />Help!!

		

		</td>
